goals.question: What is the average distance of flights?
goals.rationale: This helps to identify the median distance, the range of distances, and any outliers in the dataset.

goals.question: What is the distribution of flights by origin airport?
goals.rationale: This helps to identify the most common origin airports and any potential patterns or trends in the data.

goals.question: What is the distribution of flights by destination airport?
goals.rationale: This helps to identify the most common destination airports and any potential patterns or trends in the data.

goals.question: What is the relationship between flight delay and distance?

goals.rationale: This helps to identify any correlation between flight delay and distance, and whether longer flights tend to have more delays.

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='delay', bins=20)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.boxplot(data['distance'])
    plt.title("What is the average distance of flights?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Distance")
    plt.ylabel("Miles")
    plt.axhline(data['distance'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['distance'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    chart = sns.countplot(x='origin', data=data)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of flights by origin airport?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.countplot(data=data, x='destination', order=data['destination'].value_counts().index)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of flights by destination airport?", wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
